Why Each Additional Element Is Added
1. Additional Server

Added to separate responsibilities and improve scalability.

Benefits:

More resources available
Easier maintenance
Better fault isolation
Independent scaling of services
2. Second HAProxy (Load Balancer Cluster)

In Task 2, the load balancer was a SPOF.

Adding a second HAProxy creates high availability.

HAProxy #1 (Active)
HAProxy #2 (Standby or Active)

If one load balancer fails, the other continues serving traffic.

Benefits:

Eliminates load balancer SPOF
Improves availability
Supports failover
3. Split Components onto Dedicated Servers

Instead of mixing everything on the same machine:

Web Layer
Nginx

Responsibilities:

Serve static files
Reverse proxy requests
Handle HTTPS traffic
Application Layer
Application Server
Application Files

Responsibilities:

Execute business logic
Generate dynamic content
Database Layer
MySQL

Responsibilities:

Store and retrieve data

Benefits:

Easier scaling
Better security
Better performance
Clear separation of responsibilities
Why This Design Is Better
Better Scalability

Need more web capacity?

Add Web/App Server 3
Add Web/App Server 4

without changing the database layer.

Better Fault Tolerance
Two load balancers instead of one
Multiple application servers
Database replication available
Better Resource Utilization

Database workloads no longer compete with:

Nginx
Application processes

for CPU, RAM, and disk I/O.

Application Server vs Web Server
Web Server (Nginx)

Handles:

HTTP/HTTPS requests
Static files (CSS, JS, images)
Reverse proxying

Example:

User → Nginx
Application Server

Handles:

Business logic
Dynamic content generation
Database interactions

Example:

Nginx → Application Server → MySQL
